inn1.comm: good quick ball on the stumps, batsman is forced to defend
good stroke! Just a fraction shorter outside the off stump, he just stands and punches that through the gap in the offside for four, wasnt in total control of that shot and it runs away for four
good comeback delivery, full and swinging away from outside off stump, he drives loosely and is beaten all ends up
slightly shorter on middle and leg, stands tall and works that in front of square leg
more carry on that one as it rises from outside off stump, Chibhabha shoulders arms
another good, quick delivery outside off shapes away from Chibhabha's back-foot prod, good over from Taylor
and he begins with a full ball down the legs, umpire Benson spreads his arms to signal wide
better ball, angled into leg and it raps him on the front pad, no real appeal from any of the fielders as it was down the wrong line
drifts to leg again and its worked away to square leg's right for a run
better ball, lands on off and seams away, batsman stands and pokes at it
another good one, angled across him from off stump and this time he shoulders arms
this one lands on middle and leg and hits him high on the knee roll as he shoulders arms again, bowler appeals but that was too high, batsmen steal a leg bye to the off side
fuller on off, defended to point, call of 'NO' back to his partner
good, fullish ball on the stumps, Chibhabha defends, the ball rolls to the off side
rises from outside off, Chibhabha stands tall and steers that down past second slip for a single to third man, sensibly played
fullish on off, seams at the last moment, batsman caught in the crease defending, ends up playing it well in the end to keep the ball down
too short this time, he stands tall and punches that hard to cover, who fields well
short of a length on off stump, stands tall and defends, Taylor does the collecting
same ball, good length, stands up and drives back to the bowler
cleaned up! Bradshaw gets the first wicket with one that lands on middle and off and comes back into Chibhabha, who plays all over it and loses this middle stump

good lifter on middle and off, Masakadza is surprised by the bounce, defends and the ball trickles just past the stumps, nonstriker calls for the run and they set off, Bradshaw moves in and bumps into Mufambisi, all safe in the end
short and wide, Mufambisi cuts hard to point, Dwayne Bravo dives to his left and saves runs, brilliant stop there
fuller on middle and leg, caught hustling in his defense, keeps it out
short of a good length on middle and off, tucks it off the hips straight to square leg who moves in quickly
lands on middle and leg and moves in, catches him near the midriff, ball rolls to the off side
full and swinging away from outside off stump, keeps a tad low for the 'keeper after the batsman leaves it alone
short of a good length outside off stump, punched to cover and he shouts back to his eager partner to resist the run
slightly fuller outside off, drives loosely to cover and they think about the run but again resist

another batsman's bowled! A fine, swinging delivery that lands on a perfect length outside off stump and jags back in sharply, Masakadza is caught in his crease fishing at it and looks back to see his off stump pegged back, beaten for pace, good strike for Taylor
good, full ball on off stump, defended to the off side
swings down leg stump and called a wide
a good yorker on off, from Taylor, the bowler, is well kept out by Taylor, the batsman, end of a fine over
good length on the stumps, stands tall and punches to mid-off
stands up a bit outside off stump, Mufambisi does well to push that to cover
short and wide, crunched off the backfoot to Bravo at point
short again, loosely pushed to cover
good length ball on the stumps, does well to hustle back and defend
short and wide, does well to steer that down to Taylor at third man
good ball on off stumps, stands tall and defends, outer edge to cover

good length outside off, Mufambisi stands tall and slices that to Bravo's left at point, who dives but cant get to it, they steal two, good throw comes in quickly from Hinds but not fielded well at the stumps, Taylor gets a let-off
shorter outside off stump, stands erect and pushes that in the gap at point, ball races away to the fence, fielder in the deep dives and stops the four but they get three anyways
full on the stumps, defended
full on middle and leg, worked in front of midwicket for one, Taylor off the mark
shot! Full in the blockhole, Mufambisi gets on top of it and firmly pushes that between bowler and the stumps, ball scorches the turf and greets the long-off ropes
middle and off, defended
full outside off stump, left alone with a stride forward
shorter this time, Taylor stands tall and punches that to mid-off for one
short of a length again, stands up and drives to left of cover
fuller outside off, Mufambisi leans into it and squeezes that past point for a brace, confident shot
fullish on off stump, Taylor defends past the stumps, mid-on moves quickly and fields it
too short this time, Taylor jabs that past gully for a single down to third man
quicker on middle and leg, adjusts his shot to clip that to Bravo at square leg
tucked up with one that moves in from middle and off, worked to Lara at midwicket
shorter on off, stands and defends to the off stump

short delivery gets him a wicket! Banged in short and fast on off stump, surprised Mufambisi totally, caught in two minds - pull or hook? - but takes his eyes off it and ends up wafting, gets a touch on that and Baugh collects the catch behind the stumps, all go up in appeal and the bearded Rudi Koertzen raises the finger, Taylor gets another wicket, well bowled, West Indian style lifter
good, fullish ball on off, gets his feet well forward and defends
quicker outside off, defended to point
short of a good length, stands tall and punches to Chanderpaul at mid-off

shortish again, pushed off the back foot to Chanderpaul at short mid-off again and just sets off for the run, utter madness when the balls going right to a fielder, and Chanderpaul swoops in and fires in a direct hit at the nonstriker's end, Taylor is out by a country mile and just keeps on running back to the hut, stupid run, what was he thinking?
good, full ball on middle and leg, defended back to the bowler
good length ball on the stumps, batsman gets back and defends with a straight bat
a no-ball, full outside off and defended to cover
good length ball outside off, defends to point
short outside off stump, stands tall and defends, gets an inside edge and the ball rolls near to the stumps
again outside off stump, stands tall and defends to point
quick ball on the stumps, hustles to defend off the back foot
good length ball moves in from outside off stump, batsman quick to defend
moves in from off stump and squares him up, he hops and defends to leg
fullish outside off, gets well forward and pushes that to cover
good ball, lands outside off and seams away from his forward prod, well bowled
quicker on the stumps, batsman gets behind the line and presents a full face of the bat, ball rolls to short cover
quick on a good length on off, hustles to defend back to the bowler
short on middle and off, tries to work that fine between midwicket, ends up getting a leading edge past square leg
fullish outside off and seaming away, left alone, tidy over from Bradshaw
fullish outside off, batsman defends, gets an outer edge that bounces just in front of Sarwan at slip, close call
drifts to middle and leg and Matsikenyeri flicks that in the air past square leg, the  placement is good and he picks up four to deep backward square leg
slow on middle and off, works that in the gap at midwicket for a couple
better ball, outside off stump, defended to cover
good ball, some pace on that one, nips in from outside off and catches him high n the knee roll as he falls over, but missing the line of the stumps

gets him with a beauty! Lands on a short of a driveable length in that excellent channel, moves away just enough to draw the edge as Matsikenyeri defends it, Baugh gleefully holds the catch and Smith strikes in his first over, Zimbabwe are halfway over
fullish on off, defends to the off side
okaaaay then! This one lands somewhere well before the middle of the pitch as Bradshaw loses it in his bowling action, wide signalled
wide outside off and he has a wild swing at that and misses
wuff! Stand and deliver! Width outside off stump and Chigumbura slashes that magnificently past cover-point for four
short of a good length outside off, this time he shoulder arms
good ball on the stumps, pushed off the front foot to mid-off
angled down leg stump, very close and Koertzen doesnt call it wide
fuller on off and moving in, goes to work it fine and misses, a very good shout for leg before but Koertzen shakes his head, maybe going on too much over the stumps
full outside off, gets forward and defends to point
slighty shorter this time on middle and off, Chigumbura goes for a tame pull and gets struck in the midriff, ball rolls to the leg side
he oversteps on this occasion, needless
fullish outside off, defended to the off side
good length ball outside off, left alone by Rinke

harakiri at Motera! Drifts to middle and off, the straighter ball, works that to midwicket and sets off for the run, Chigumbura sends him back, but Hinds is too smooth here and fires in a throw that catches the big boy Rinke just short of his crease, another run out for Zimbabwe
full on the stumps, defends to the off side
fullish outside off stump, leans into it and square drives that past point for two
lands outside off and seams away, beats his poke at that one
too full and its driven to cover for a sharp single
short and wide, stands tall and steers that behind point for two more
fullish this time, leans into it and pushes that in the gap at cover for two more
full on the stumps, defended to point
full again, pushed to mid-off again
middle and off line this time, pushed to midwicket, no chance of a run
fullish and its driven to Chanderpaul at short mid-off
drifts to middle and leg, nicely clipped past square leg for four, confident shot
shortish outside off stump, leaves it alone
good ball on the stumps, defended to the covers
full again, defended to the off side
full once more, pushed in front of covers
middle and leg, worked in front of midwicket, no run though
middle and leg again, looks to flick, struck on the pads, Smith collects quickly
quicker yorker, in the blockhole, does well to dig it out to the onside
short of a good length on the stumps, quickly defended to the off side
what was that? Not a short delivery at all but he goes for an ugly pull across the line and gets beaten all ends up

there you have it, madness, I tell you! Elton Chigumbura went for a stupid swipe the ball before, clearly he didn't learn a thing, tries to smoke a short-of-a-good-length delivery outside off stump into oblivion, doesnt get under it and ends up spooning a simple catch to Taylor at mid-off who only has to take a few steps back and pouch it, Zimbabwe slip even further, how much longer will this innings last?
fullish outside off, defends quickly to point
middle and off line, looks to work across the line, doesnt make contact
drifts to middle and leg, clipped to Hinds at square leg
fuller on middle and leg, drives but gets an inside edge that races past backward square leg and just beats Marlon Samuels' feeble football-style stop on the ropes, useful runs for Zimbabwe

shorter outside off, he goes after it and the ball pops up towards a diving Sarwan at second slip, they all go up in appeal but the umpire shakes his head and hands the cap n shades back to the bowler, did he not make contact on that one?
full on the stumps, defended
full again, hustles to defend
good ball, lands on a sweet spot outside off and seams past Ireland's backfoot prod
hits that spot again moves in a tad, Ireland has to stand and defend
lands outside off and stays low, Ireland stands and defends to point
fullish on off, defends and gets an inside edge to short mid-on, a maiden over to Smith, well bowled
full on the stumps, defended back to Bravo
short and wide, nicely driven with a flourish in the gap at extra cover for one
fuller and quicker on middle and leg, moves into him as he drops that bat on it
middle and off, worked straight to midwicket
bounces him on middle and leg and he goes down on his haunches
quick on a good length outside off, Ireland defends awkwardly and the ball balloons up towards cover but lands safely in front of Lara
middle and off, defended to mid-on who moves in quickly
fullish outside off, steered down past gully for one to third man
well wide of off stump and its left alone
good length ball on the stumps, defended down to point
fullish on off, Ireland tries to drive and gets an inside edge to the leg side
again this one's on the stumps and he gets his defense correct, ball trickles to point
short and wide, he moves forward and squeezes that behind point for two, Taylor moves around from third man and fields on the ropes
fullish and its pushed to the cover region, Lara fields
fullish again, a good-looking drive in the gap at mid-off and cover, they pick up another run
short of a good length outside off, Ireland leans into and drives firmly in the gap on the off side, ball speeds away for four, good runs for Zimbabwe
good ball, lands outside off on a good length, and beats his forward  prod
slower delivery, loops down into him and he manages to defend to the off side
tossed up on off, defended with caution
flatter this time, batsman gets forward and defends
middle and leg line, Utseya sweeps and gets bat on it, ball runs away fine and they get a brace
fuller outside off, defended off the front foot
off stump again, defended
and again, defended to the off side
bouncer and ducked under without any fuss.
outside edge to third man. It was fullish on the off and he pushed at it
on the legs, flicked past midwicket
on the off ,a length delivery and patted back.
That slower ball of Bravo. Released between the thumb and the forefinger. lands outside off and he steered it fine to the third man fence. Off the front foot. Nice looking shot.
leans forward , head over the ball, taps it to cover

Gentle off break, did nothing dramatic and that was the secret. Ireland pushed at it , expecting it would turn in sharply - why he thought so, only he would know- and ended up playing inside the line. Landed just outside off stump and hit off. As simple as it gets. I think I caught a sheepish grin pastered on Gayle.
full and outside off, steered to backward point
almost another tame dismissal. Again a gentle loopy delivery on the middle and Rainsford almost scooped it to short midwicket
fullish on the off and middle, played back down the track
delivered from around the stumps. Full and outside off, almost in the blockhole, the batsman almost contrived to get out. Attempted to steer it - there is a slip standing- but misses
on a length outside off, pushed to cover point
again just outside off, pushed to point.
deja-vu at Motera. All the four balls in this over have brought Dwayne Smith at point in to play.
Looping slower one. ends up as a low dipping full-toss, Rainsford, surprised, manages to keep that one out
Bravo continues to perfect his slower one. Another one on the middle, slow loopy low full-toss, pushed out, not so convincingly, to the off side
tossed up outside off, perfect forward defensive stroke
leans forward to a tossed-up delivery outside off and pushes it towards point
driven to mid-off

sharp catch by Bravo at first slip. It was tossed up outside off, turned in a bit and bounced a little. Rainsford goes for a cut and is beaten by the extra bounce. It darted to the left of Bravo who pouches it smartly
banged in short, it rears up throat high and fended off ungainly
upper-cut to third man but Utseya doesn't want the single. Wants to keep the strike, considering how the last two wickets fell, tamely, can't really blame him.
fullish, pushed back to the bowler
he will retain the strike by drilling a slower one out to long-off
And Utseya falls and ZImbabwe have folded up for a meagre 85. He went for a pull  but missed.

inn2.comm: fullish outside off, Gayle defends to cover
moves from outside off away for the 'keeper to collect, Gayle not interested in that one
short of a good length outside off, good bounce, Gayle stands up and punches to cover
angles down the pads, clipped down to fine leg
full outside off, Chanderpaul hurries to defend to the off side
drifts to leg again, Chanderpaul works that down to fine leg for one, off the mark
hint of swing there. Slanted across and it swung away but too early in its trajectory to tease Chanderpaul
again swings away, again bit too early. ends up as a low full-toss, pushed to off side.
edged past the slips. That one squared-up Chanders. Landed on a length, swing and seam movement.
another one in the channel outsidse off. Good swinging delivery, if only he can get it to swing late... he can be in business.
pushed across Chanderpaul, who lets it go through.
low full-toss outside off, hint of swing, pushed past covers. It hit the toe-end of the bat, else it would have sped to the fence
hits the deck on a length outside the leg stump, and moves across Chanderpaul who stands up tall to gently tap it down in front of him
punched back down the track and the mid-off fielder misfields it, yielding a run
hits the deck on a length outside off stump and shapes away
in the corridor outside off, left alone
Chanderpaul is standing outside his crease. It was fullish, on the off stump line, pushed to the off side
slips through harmlessly outside the off stump, no shot offered.
drifting down the leg side. Attempted to swing it in and ends up dragging it down a bit. Not too much but umpires are always harsh on the leg side
weak appeal for lbw. lands on the leg stump line and straightens and chanderpaul is rapped on the pads as he misses his attempted flick
surprise bouncer, Gayle tries to pull it, ends up looking ungainly, but gets a run, courtesy a top edge
angled across Gayle but it lands outside off stump and veers further away.
much better line. Landed on a length on the off and shaped away, steered, away from his body, to gully
Gayle shapes up for his booming square-drive but the ball bounces a bit more than he expected. Also not much room and he ends up pushing it to point
outside off, left alone
wide outside off, left alone
again well outside the off stump, left alone.
on the legs, tucked behind square-leg
Gayle attempts to break free with a forcing thump but couldn't get much power behind that stroke and the point fielder moves to his left to make the stop
again the bottom-hand comes into play and kills the power. The ball rolls to cover
fullish on the off, driven on-the-up to mid-off
on the off, pushed to mid-off
Both Gayle and the wicketkeeper, Taylor missed that one. Gayle misses his pull and Taylor gets a bad bounce
leans forward to a length delivery outside off and pushes it to cover
beaten in his offdrive. He ends up driving outside the line as the ball lands outside off and straightens.
Although he didn't quite reach to the pitch of the ball, he went for his half-drive, half-punched shot through the covers.
banged in short and it rises throat high at Chanderpaul who jabs at it.
slanted across, left alone
just outside off, Chanderpaul, initially, shapes to play but pulls out
on the leg and middle. tucked to square-leg
worked to the on side
fullish outside off, dabbed to backward point
Finally, after a lolling for some time, Gayle wakes up. Bang. He rocks back to pull a short of length delivery high and handsome over midwicket.
Unfurls a pre-determined pull. He kept his front foot outside the line and pulled over midwicket
thwack. overpitched on the stumps and Gayle crashes it straight at the bowler who manages to half-stop it.
Ah.... caressed past the short fine-leg fielder. Full and on the legs, tickled past that fielder
tip and run. just tapped close on the off side.
Chanderpaul is squared-up as he pushes at a delivery that lands on the leg and moves across him. The leading edge takes the ball towards point
Good ball but unluckily for him he yields a bounary. It was a yorker and Gayle got his bat down in a hurry and got an inside edge
dropped by Utseya, the captain, running back from mid-off. Gayle had gone for a pre-determined pull and had skied that edge but ...
smoked over midwicket. no mistake this time. Again bit pre-determined.
swing and a miss. It would have gone into the city bazaar - Motera ground is 10 kms away from the city- had he connected.
crash. on the legs and he swings it nonchalantly to long-leg
Another drop. This time at squarish third man. Another pre-determined pull gets a top edge but Ireland at thirdman drops a rather simple catch. Two missed chances in the over
One-handed swat over mid-on. As if he was swatting a fly away. Full and outside off, he went for his drive and the bottom-hand came off the bat-handle and the top hand steered it over mid-on
drifting down the leg side. If it was not a no-ball it would have been declared a wide.
slower delivery outside off, fullish, dug out back to the bowler
straying on to the leg and middle, nonchalantly flicked past square-leg
Three fielders - mid-on, midwicket and long-off converge in for a catch but it lands right in the middle of them. Another pull that went awry
Gayle finally falls. he had tried numerous times to get out and he succeeds this time. Another pull attempted off a ball that wasn't that short and the resultant skier was held at midwicket
Chanderpaul makes sure that Lara will be on strike the next over. Good.
Aha! that famous whiplash square-drive has been unfurled first ball.
on the leg stump line, Lara is beaten in his forward prod and it raps him on the pads
Utseya continues to toss it up. outside off and Lara goes for a cover drive, gets ani inside edge that takes the ball to midwicket
leans forward to dead-bat a tossed-up delivery on the off and middle
Utseya dares to flight again - he is a pretty good offspinner as his record shows - driven to sweeper cover
angled across Lara, left alone
Lara hops back and across and almost ends up playing over the ball. It kept a touch low and hits the bottom-half of the bat
moves back and across, pushes it to cover
bit of width outside off and Lara jumps at the opportunity and unleashes a square-drive past point
on the off stump line, pushed to point.
yes sir, single it is. full and outside off, Lara moves towards it to drive it to deep cover. Will keep the strike!
comes down the track, Utseya drags back the length and Lara has to be contended in just pushing it away
swept past square-leg . Utseya is bowling pretty well, keeping the great batsman in check.
lands on the off and middle and spuns past Lara who lets it go through
Chanderpaul walks into his shot -a push to point.
steered to backward point.
back of length , on the off, pushed to point
again pushed to point. Chanderpaul looks to be in no hurry.
pushed across, left alone
There you go, he waltzs down the track and lofts it over widish long-on.
Lara finishes it off in style. Obviously , he doesn't want to mope around in the pavilion for the lunch break. Glides down the track, to the pitch, and deposits it over long-on.
